deployBattlePass(uint256).notice: Deploys a new BattlePass which supports a specific underlying creatorId.

getBattlePassFromUnderlying(uint256).notice: Computes a BattlePass's address from its accepted underlying creatorId

isBattlePassDeployed(address).notice: Returns if a BattlePass at an address has already been deployed.

BattlePassDeployed(address,uint256).notice: Emitted when a new BattlePass is deployed.

userdoc.notice: Factory which enables deploying a BattlePass for any creatorId

deployBattlePass(uint256).details: This will revert if a BattlePass that accepts the same underlying creatorId has already been deployed.

params.creatorId: The creatorId that the BattlePass should accept.

getBattlePassFromUnderlying(uint256).details: The BattlePass returned may not be deployed yet. Use isBattlePassDeployed to check.

params.creatorId: The creatorId that the BattlePass should accept.

returns._0: The address of a BattlePass which accepts the provided underlying creatorId.

isBattlePassDeployed(address).details: This function is useful to check the return values of getBattlePassFromUnderlying, as it does not check that the BattlePass addresses it computes have been deployed yet.

params.bp: The address of a BattlePass which may not have been deployed yet.

returns._0: A boolean indicating whether the BattlePass has been deployed already.

params.creatorId: The underlying creatorId the new BattlePass accepts.
